author: julianfoad
msg: Fix unnecessary sleeping after a copy or move, following r1463721.
In r1463721, I stopped passing a specific path to the sleep function,
which meant it could no longer choose a sleep appropriate to the
file system and so might sleep longer than necessary; and I also
failed to initialize the 'sleep required' flag to false, which meant it
might sleep even after copying to a URL.
* subversion/libsvn_client/copy.c
(try_copy): Document the 'timestamp_sleep' parameter.
(svn_client_copy6, svn_client_move7): Initialize the flag.
Pass the destination path to the sleep function.
Found by: philip
